WORRIED by the regularity of fraud-related investments in the creative sub-sector of the economy, the Registrar/Chief Executive of Advertising Practitioners Council of Nigeria (APCON), Dr. Olalekan Fadolapo and his counterpart at the Director General of National Broadcasting Commission (NBC), Mallam Balarabe Ilelah recently paid a courtesy visit to the Chairman of Economic & Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) Mr Abdulrasheed Bawa at the EFCC Headquarters in Abuja, where they impressed on the latter the need to forge a synergy of cooperation in the interest of the industry. Specifically, the duo solicited the support of the anti-graft agency to help in sanitising the media/advertising industry and eliminate iniquitous activities of some operators in the sector which have been crippling the development and growth of the industry.   Buhari reconstitutes board of Federal Mortgage Bank     Port Harcourt refinery to start operation next year     Nigeria boosts maritime strength with diversification   According to the NBC and APCON bosses, the fraudulent activities of some stakeholders and huge advertising debt have generated concerns as these have created operational challenges for the industry. Most media houses are crippled operationally as obtaining credit under false pretense and other fraudulent activities of some stakeholders are endangering the growth of the industry. Citing the critical roles played by the Commission in curbing the menace of fraud within the nation’s financial institutions, the duo said they were convinced that the intervention of the EFCC is strategic to the success of the ongoing industry reforms within the creative sub-sector. Responding, the EFCC Czar reiterated the Commission’s zero tolerance for corruption and financial crimes in the country just as he pledged the commitment of the EFCC in supporting the advertising industry and indicated that two Desk Offices will be created in Abuja and Lagos by the Commission for the industry intervention.